        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 8 at 3:59AM MDT by NWS Rapid City SD</headline>
        <description>At 359 AM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 3
miles east of Slim Buttes, or 24 miles southeast of Buffalo, moving
northeast at 45 mph.

HAZARD...Penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor hail damage to vegetation is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Bison, Reva, Lodgepole, Sorum, Prairie City, Slim Buttes, Sheep
Buttes, and southern Shadehill Reservoir.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
